  "label": "Fulgurite Echo Cavern",
  "description": "Fulgurite Echo Cavern is a basalt-throated cave cut into the Ashmantle Range, its walls lacquered with vitrified cinder and impact glass. Veins of lightning-fused fulgurite stitch the stone in pale, brittle seams that catch and scatter the bruise-lit auroral glow at the entrance. The floor is choked with black scree and glassy shards that grind under pressure and hold a persistent metallic tang. Mineral density and storm-born interference deaden vox transmission, reducing sound to close, hard reflections within the chambers.",
